Engine

Class GameObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • Engine.GameObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BarMeter, GridElement, Particle, ParticleList, RepairMeter, RowMeter

    public class GameObject
extends java.lang.Object
    GameObject, base class of all game objects that encapsulate all common behaviors of objects in the game.

      • pixelTouches

        public boolean pixelTouches(GameObject other)
        Test if the textures of two GameObject overlaps. **WARNING**: this can be a very expensive function to call. Make sure the parameter is the smaller texuter is making the call: smallerTextureGameObject.pixelTouches(largerTextureGameObject);
        Parameters:
        other - the other GameObject to be tested for intersection (should be the object with larger texture)
        Returns:
        true if the two textures has any non-transparent region that overlaps, false otherwise

      • setSpriteSheet

        public void setSpriteSheet(java.lang.String spriteFilename,
                           int width,
                           int height,
                           int totalFrames,
                           int ticksPerFrame)
        Sets up the spritesheet animation. Will not do anything if width, height, or totalFrame are less than 0.
        Parameters:
        spriteFilename - Filename of the spritesheet image
        width - Width of individual sprite.
        height - Height of individual sprite.
        totalFrames - Total sprites in spritesheet
        ticksPerFrame - How long each sprite remains before the next is drawn.

      • setSpriteSheet

        public void setSpriteSheet(java.awt.image.BufferedImage image,
                           int width,
                           int height,
                           int totalFrames,
                           int ticksPerFrame)
        Sets up the spritesheet animation. Will not do anything if width, height, or totalFrame are less than 0.
        Parameters:
        image - The bufferedTexture (image) of the spritesheet
        width - Width of individual sprite.
        height - Height of individual sprite.
        totalFrames - Total sprites in spritesheet
        ticksPerFrame - How long each sprite remains before the next is drawn.

      • setAnimationPauseStatus

      • setToDrawOutline

        public void setToDrawOutline(boolean onlyOutlined)
        controls the drawing of the GameObject to only drawing outline or not. Default: fills.
        Parameters:
        onlyOutlined - if true only draws outlined, otherwise draws regular (filled)

      • setAutoDrawTo

        public void setAutoDrawTo(boolean autoDraw)
        Default behavior of GameObject is that it will be drawn automatically for each frame. You can switch this off by setting autodraw to false.
        Parameters:
        autoDraw - true: draw automatically, false: do not draw this game object

      • draw

        public void draw()
        Draws this game object. if setAutoDrawTo(true), then, this object will be drawn twice per frame. GameObject's draw should not be called explicitly (AutoDraw will take care of drawing!)
